Human briefing

Purpose:
- Human-facing clarification brief for the MemoryEndpoints.com UAIX handoff package.

Verification status: active operational briefing; verify with `AGENTS.md`, `workspace.uai`, and `.uai/startup-packet.uai` before relying on it.
Memory scope: human clarification needs, approval boundaries, and what agents will defend.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: update this briefing when human-facing assumptions, approvals, or escalation boundaries change.
Source of truth: current human instructions, `AGENTS.md`, `workspace.uai`, and the active `.uai` suite.
Next action for agents: read this after `AGENTS.md` and before broad local memory loading when a human briefing is useful.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, private handoff payloads, raw one-time keys, private deployment values, or hidden customer data.

Human needs to know:
- This repository uses the published UAIX file set for code-bearing Project Handoff plus Agent File Handoff plus MATM durable-memory routing.
- Active `.uai` files are date-free and public-safe.
- MemoryEndpoints.com is the real MATM endpoint; MultiAgentMemory.com is the companion documentation site.
- Live deployment and live companion publishing remain blocked by external FTPS access, not by local code evidence.
- README.md files are human documentation only. The memory package lives in `.uai`.
- `short-term-memory.uai` and `current-state.uai` are forbidden here under the updated UAIX direction from the human; their facts belong in typed files such as context, progress, next-actions, decisions, constraints, and test-plan.
